The total number of ways to draw 5 cards from a deck of 52 is calculated using combinations. The formula for combinations is C(n, k) = n! / [k!(n - k)!], where n is the total number of items, k is the number of items to choose, and "!" denotes factorial, which is the product of all positive integers up to that number. So, the total number of ways to draw 5 cards from 52 is C(52, 5).

