## Step 6: Calculate the energy to stretch three carbon-carbon double bonds to $1.397 Å$
First, convert $1.335 Å$ to meters: $1.335 Å = 1.335 \times 10^{-10} m$. The energy to stretch one double bond is $\frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (1.397 \times 10^{-10} - 1.335 \times 10^{-10})^2$. Calculate this energy.

