$E_{\text{double}} = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (1.397 \times 10^{-10} - 1.335 \times 10^{-10})^2 = \frac{1}{2} \times 950 \times (0.062 \times 10^{-10})^2 = 0.5 \times 950 \times 0.3844 \times 10^{-22} = 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} J$.

## Step 8: Calculate the total energy to stretch three carbon-carbon double bonds
$E_{\text{3 double}} = 3 \times E_{\text{double}} = 3 \times 1.8259 \times 10^{-20} = 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} J$.

## Step 9: Calculate the total energy for both compressing single bonds and stretching double bonds
$E_{\text{total}} = E_{\text{3 single}} + E_{\text{3 double}} = 1.326675 \times 10^{-19} + 5.4777 \times 10^{-20} = 1.874445 \times 10^{-19} J$.

## Step 10: Convert the total energy from Joules to $\mathrm{kcal} / \mathrm{mol}$
First, recall that $1 \mathrm{~kcal} = 4184 J$ and Avogadro's number is $6.022 \times 10^{23} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}$. The conversion factor is $\frac{1 \mathrm{~kcal}}{4184 J} \times \frac{6.022 \times 10^{23}}{1 \mathrm{~mol}}$. Thus, $E_{\text{total}} \text{ in } \mathrm{kcal}/\mathrm{mol} = \frac{1.874445 \times 10^{-19} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23}}{4184}$.

## Step 11: Perform the conversion calculation
$E_{\text{total}} \text{ in } \mathrm{kcal}/\mathrm{mol} = \frac{1.874445 \times 10^{-19} \times 6.022 \times 10^{23}}{4184} = \frac{1.1289 \times 10^{5}}{4184} = 26.98 \approx 27 \mathrm{~kcal}/\mathrm{mol}$.

