$P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453) = P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50)$, where $Z$ is a standard normal variable.

## Step 4: Calculate $P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50)$ using the standard normal distribution
$P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50) = P(Z \leq 0.50) - P(Z \leq -1.50)$.
Using a standard normal distribution table:
- $P(Z \leq 0.50) \approx 0.6915$
- $P(Z \leq -1.50) \approx 0.0668$
So, $P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50) = 0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247$.

